  "text_preview": "\"hard of hearing\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► Make an \"H\" handshape and drop it a few inches, have it bounce up and over to the right and back down again in a small arc. Sort of like drawing a lowercase \"n\" in the air with an \"H\" handshape. HARD-OF-HEARING: Sample sentence: \"Do you think hard-of-hearing people should marry Deaf people or Hearing people?\" = YOU THINK HARD-OF-HEARING SHOULD MARRY DEAF O-R HEARING? You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars"
